The paper deals with the performance analysis of energy detection for wireless communication systems, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The analysis also involves the use of statistical models and distributions, which can be related to systems and control (cs.SY) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper uses mathematical techniques to derive novel expressions and models, which can be associated with mathematics (cs.MA).
